Mikado is an established tradition on Georgia St in Indianapolis. It hosts NFL head coaches and owners, GenCon luminaries, and lots and lots of discerning sushi and Japanese cuisine fans. From katsu bowls, to bento boxes, to rolls and nigiri, they have you covered in style and quality. Sometimes, they have special events, with limited menus, so it's worth checking out their social media for such treats. I personally like the Hoosier Damburi Bowl at lunch, fantastic, filling, just great. I'm not a huge sushi eater but what I have gotten is always good and pretty. My photos include the limited offering Ramen. The pork belly just melted and was exceptional. Then the signature whitefish roll, draped with delicious crab. Also the special Tofu and Pork sandos, both delicious, but the tofu was stand alone good, so light and moist with a great crisp breading and then finally a seaweed salad, which I personally don't like, but my daughter just loves. They even give her assisted chopsticks so she doesn't have to use a fork and that is just a great extra step. Thanks!
Enjoyed going here. Staff friendly and attentive. Food was wonderful. I highly recommend the mystery roll. It was amazing. Everything was very good. If in town, would go again.

$$$. Mikado is the best place for sushi in Indiana. They use incredibly fresh ingredients in all their dishes, with meticulous attention to taste, texture, temperature and presentation, in a very comfortable, serene and relaxing environment, with very attentive service from all their staff. They also offer sushi bar seating, that allows the dinners to interact directly with the sushi chefs and see firsthand the level of care, precision and skill involved in making really fantastic sushi, sashimi and sushi rolls. You simply can't go wrong in selecting this place to dine and experience really authentic Japanese cuisine and a lovely dining experience. The only downside is parking is very limited and expensive since they are located downtown. Many elect to drop-off their party at the door and then go hunt for parking nearby.
